This project focuses on analyzing a retail Superstore dataset using Microsoft Excel to understand sales performance and business trends.
The dataset includes information such as order date, region, category, sales, quantity, and profit.
Data cleaning was performed to remove duplicates and ensure proper formatting. 
Pivot tables, filters, and Excel charts were used to analyze sales by region, category, and time.
The analysis helped identify top-performing product categories, high-sales regions, and profit patterns. 
Visualizations such as bar charts, pie charts, and line charts were created to clearly present the insights. 
The project demonstrates how Excel can be used for data analysis to support business decisions and improve sales
